    <title>Java environment variable configuration</title>
    <link href="/2025/07/05/Java-environment-variable-configuration/"/>
    <url>/2025/07/05/Java-environment-variable-configuration/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<blockquote><p>网络上的教学太杂乱了，有时候重装电脑后需要安装Idea都花费很多时间，因此有此篇文章。</p></blockquote><hr><h2 id="✅-Full-Guide-Installing-Java-JDK-and-Configuring-Environment-Variables-on-Windows-11"><a href="#✅-Full-Guide-Installing-Java-JDK-and-Configuring-Environment-Variables-on-Windows-11" class="headerlink" title="✅ Full Guide: Installing Java JDK and Configuring Environment Variables on Windows 11"></a>✅ Full Guide: Installing Java JDK and Configuring Environment Variables on Windows 11</h2><h3 id="🔧-Step-1-Download-and-Install-Java-JDK"><a href="#🔧-Step-1-Download-and-Install-Java-JDK" class="headerlink" title="🔧 Step 1: Download and Install Java JDK"></a>🔧 Step 1: Download and Install Java JDK</h3><ol><li><p>Visit the official Java website:</p><ul><li><p>Oracle JDK: <a href="https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase-downloads.html">https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase-downloads.html</a></p></li><li><p>Or use OpenJDK: <a href="https://jdk.java.net/">https://jdk.java.net</a></p></li></ul></li><li><p>Download the installer and run it. During installation:</p><ul><li><p>Click <strong>Next</strong> to accept the default settings.</p></li><li><p>You may change the install path, but it’s recommended to use the default:</p>  <figure class="highlight livescript"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs livescript">C:<span class="hljs-string">\Program</span> Files<span class="hljs-string">\Java\jdk-XX</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ul></li></ol><hr><h3 id="⚙️-Step-2-Configure-Environment-Variables"><a href="#⚙️-Step-2-Configure-Environment-Variables" class="headerlink" title="⚙️ Step 2: Configure Environment Variables"></a>⚙️ Step 2: Configure Environment Variables</h3><h4 id="✅-2-1-Set-JAVA-HOME"><a href="#✅-2-1-Set-JAVA-HOME" class="headerlink" title="✅ 2.1 Set JAVA_HOME"></a>✅ 2.1 Set <code>JAVA_HOME</code></h4><ol><li><p>Press <code>Windows + S</code> and search for “Environment Variables”.<br> Click on <strong>Edit the system environment variables</strong> → then click <strong>Environment Variables</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Under <strong>System variables</strong>, click <strong>New…</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Variable name</strong>: <code>JAVA_HOME</code></p></li><li><p><strong>Variable value</strong>: your JDK install path (e.g.):</p>  <figure class="highlight livescript"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs livescript">C:<span class="hljs-string">\Program</span> Files<span class="hljs-string">\Java\jdk-21</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ul></li><li><p>Click <strong>OK</strong> to save.</p></li></ol><hr><h4 id="✅-2-2-Add-Java-to-the-Path-Variable"><a href="#✅-2-2-Add-Java-to-the-Path-Variable" class="headerlink" title="✅ 2.2 Add Java to the Path Variable"></a>✅ 2.2 Add Java to the <code>Path</code> Variable</h4><ol><li><p>In the <strong>System variables</strong> list, find and select <code>Path</code>, then click <strong>Edit</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Click <strong>New</strong>, and add:</p> <figure class="highlight haml"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs haml"><span class="hljs-tag">%<span class="hljs-selector-tag">JAVA_HOME</span></span>%\bin<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ol><blockquote><p>⚠️ Note: You may see tutorials recommending <code>%JAVA_HOME%\jre\bin</code> — <strong>this is outdated</strong>.<br>Starting from <strong>JDK 9 and above</strong>, the JRE is integrated into the JDK, so there’s no separate <code>jre</code> folder.</p></blockquote><hr><h4 id="⚠️-2-3-Optional-Set-CLASSPATH"><a href="#⚠️-2-3-Optional-Set-CLASSPATH" class="headerlink" title="⚠️ 2.3 (Optional) Set CLASSPATH"></a>⚠️ 2.3 (Optional) Set <code>CLASSPATH</code></h4><p>Only needed for certain legacy tools (e.g., old Tomcat, Ant). Most modern setups <strong>do not require this</strong>.</p><p>If needed:</p><ol><li><p>Click <strong>New</strong> under System variables.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Variable name</strong>: <code>CLASSPATH</code></p></li><li><p><strong>Variable value</strong>:</p>  <figure class="highlight mel"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs mel">.;%JAVA_HOME%\lib\dt.jar;%JAVA_HOME%\lib\tools.jar;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ul></li></ol><blockquote><p>✅ <code>.</code> refers to the current directory.<br>⚠️ Starting from JDK 9+, <code>tools.jar</code> and <code>dt.jar</code> may not exist anymore — so skip this if using JDK 9+.</p></blockquote><hr><h3 id="🧪-Step-3-Verify-the-Setup"><a href="#🧪-Step-3-Verify-the-Setup" class="headerlink" title="🧪 Step 3: Verify the Setup"></a>🧪 Step 3: Verify the Setup</h3><ol><li><p>Open <strong>Command Prompt</strong></p></li><li><p>Run the following commands:</p></li></ol><figure class="highlight cmd"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs cmd">java -version<br>javac -version<br><span class="hljs-built_in">echo</span> <span class="hljs-variable">%JAVA_HOME%</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>✅ If the installation was successful, you’ll see the Java version and your environment variables printed correctly.</p><hr><h2 id="📌-Summary"><a href="#📌-Summary" class="headerlink" title="📌 Summary"></a>📌 Summary</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Variable</th><th>Required</th><th>Example Value</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>JAVA_HOME</code></td><td>✅ Yes</td><td><code>C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-21</code></td><td>Points to JDK directory</td></tr><tr><td><code>Path</code></td><td>✅ Yes</td><td><code>%JAVA_HOME%\bin</code></td><td>Allows using <code>java</code>, <code>javac</code> from terminal</td></tr><tr><td><code>CLASSPATH</code></td><td>⚠️ Optional</td><td><code>.;%JAVA_HOME%\lib\dt.jar;%JAVA_HOME%\lib\tools.jar;</code></td><td>Only for legacy setups</td></tr></tbody></table>]]></content>
    
    
    
